---

<MainLayout title="Outreach" description="From mentorship to collaboration with the community, Ultro Robotics is committed to more than just building robots.">
	<Paragraph slot="subtitle">
		Ultro is committed to more than just building robots. Our holistic
		approach to connecting with the community enables everyone to <strong
			class="whitespace-nowrap">engineer for humanity.</strong
		>
	</Paragraph>
	<Marquee text={["IN CONSTRUCTION", "Â·"]} />
	<section class="relative flex justify-center my-16 w-full">
		<div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center content-start gap-4 w-auto">
			<Card title="Intro to Engineering">
				<p slot="description">
					We created the ongoing 10<sup>th</sup> Grade curriculum class
					<em>Intro to Engineering</em> to acquaint sophomores with robotics,
					as well as <strong
						>increase interest in and visibility</strong
					> of the sport.
				</p>
			</Card>
			<Card title="FLL Mentoring">
				<p slot="description">
					We mentor FLL Team 65186 Panthers to teach them the
					iterative design process, spark joy & nurture interest in
					the FIRST sport of robotics.
				</p>
			</Card>
			<Card title="Scrimmage">
				<p slot="description">
					Our annual scrimmage at The Browning School hosts teams
					eager to collaborate, exchange ideas & expand learning.
				</p>
			</Card>
			<Card title="FTC Collaboration">
				<p slot="description">
					For the 2024-25 season, Ultro team members mentored the
					rookie team 22053 Liberty Robotics and collaborated with
					all-girls 13334 Spence Light Sabers.
				</p>
			</Card>
			<Card title="Ultro Robotics YouTube">
				<p slot="description">
					In response to the struggles and lack of resources faced by
					developing teams, we collaborated with NYC FIRST to develop
					a video series explaining challenging concepts. <Link
						href="https://www.youtube.com/@UltroRobotics"
						>Visit our channel!</Link
					>
				</p>
			</Card>
			<Card title="Speaker Series">
				<p slot="description">
					Our ENGINEERING FOR HUMANITY speaker series connects Ultro
					with the greater STEM community and serves as a vital part
					of team learning.
				</p>
			</Card>
		</div>
	</section>
</MainLayout>
